      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs are a government-imposed tax on imported goods, intended to protect domestic industries by making their products more competitive. However, the effect of tariffs on consumers is often the opposite, as the increased cost is typically passed on through higher prices, reducing consumer purchasing power. This can lead to trade deficits, reduced economic growth, and possible retaliatory tariffs from other countries, creating a downward spiral. Historical examples, such as the 1930s Smoot-Hawley Tariff Act, demonstrate the potential negative consequences of tariffs on the global economy.",
